  "body": "Description\r\n\r\nType: Bug\r\n\r\nSummary: When a user inputs a big amount of text, that consists of more than one line, switches to a different chat, and comes back - all besides that firs line of text is not displayed until you click on the area where it's supposed to be.\r\n\r\nExpected behavior\r\n\r\nThere should be no issues with how text is displayed\r\n\r\nActual behavior\r\n\r\nAll text besides the firs line of text, is not displayed until you click on the area where it's supposed to be\r\n\r\nReproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce:**\r\n1) Open Status desktop\r\n2) Go to 1-1 chat\r\n3) Input a long amount of text, so that it forms more than 1 line in the input message box\r\n4) Switch to a different chat for about 3 seconds\r\n5) Go back to the previous chat and check out how your input area is displayed\r\nNote: After you click on the area where the rest of your message is supposed to be, it is displayed.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1024\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/46678301-05cfeb00-cbed-11e8-8ebb-6e138af9767d.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1025\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/46678351-2009c900-cbed-11e8-9247-7f648575edae.png\">\r\n\r\nAdditional Information:\r\n\r\nStatus version: nightly 09/10/2018\r\nOperating System: Mac Sox",
